<TEXT>
<P>
Calling him "one of the most dangerous criminals to come out of society," a 
district attorney has urged Kings County residents to sign a petition opposing 
parole for Booker T. Hillery, convicted twice of murdering a Hanford girl 27 
years ago. Dist. Atty. Garry Gonzalves was one of many county law enforcement 
officials backing the petition drive prompted byHillery's 10th parole hearing 
June 22. Fifteen thousand people signed the first petition circulated for a 
parole hearing after Hillery was sentenced to a life term two years ago on his 
