<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A mint-condition example of Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec's 1891 music hall poster 
"Moulin Rouge" set a world poster auction record of $220,000 during a 
$1.2-million auction of 540 rare posters in New York. The 30-square-foot 
lithograph was sold to an American private collector who asked to remain 
anonymous. The previous world auction record for a poster was $95,000 paid in 
1987 for another example of "Moulin Rouge" in Paris. The poster, advertising 
"concert and dancing every night," shows the popular entertainer La Goulue -- 
"The Glutton" -- dancing the can-can. 
