<TEXT>
<P>
The Philadelphia Public Health Department will allow bathhouses, adult 
bookstores and adult movie theaters to remain open as long as customers are 
provided with free condoms and AIDS prevention information, according to a 
published report. The Philadelphia Inquirer detailed the department's official 
policy, which was made public Friday through the city's AIDS Activities 
Coordinating Office. The policy differs from those in cities such as San 
Francisco, where health officials closed down bathhouses because of evidence 
that sex between strangers there was spreading the AIDS virus, the Inquirer 
said. 
