<TEXT>
<P>
Harcourt Brace Jovanovich: The Orlando,Fla.-based publishing, theme park and 
insurance company reported a first-quarter net loss of $116 million, compared 
to a $35.3-million loss a year ago. Revenue rose to $315.5 million from $276.6 
million. The company said the loss in its publishing group increased by about 
$19 million over the year before. Its parks group, which includes Sea World, 
performed better than in the same period last year, the firm said, as did its 
insurance group. 
</P>
