<P>
NIGHT STALKER SUSPECT YELLS AT PRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Accused Night Stalker Richard Ramirez, who has made several courtroom 
outbursts, yelled at reporters today, calling them "sensation-seeking 
parasites." 
</P>
<P>
Ramirez's outburst occurred as he was led away by bailiffs to a lockup area 
next to the court where his trial is taking place. As the accused serial killer 
was led past a section of the court set aside for reporters and camera crews, 
he turned to them, growled and yelling at the top of his lungs, said: "Media. 
Sensation-seeking parasites." 
</P>
<P>
He was led away with no further incident. 
</P>
