<P>
MAN BEATEN AFTER HIS CAR HITS GIRL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man who accidentally struck a 4-year-old girl who had run in front of his car 
was in serious condition today after a severe beating by several men, including 
the girl's father, police said. 
</P>
<P>
James Letts, 22, was in Holy Cross Hospital with fractures of the skull, nose 
and cheekbone, a nursing supervisor said. The girl was treated for minor 
injuries at Holy Cross and released. 
</P>
<P>
Letts's auto struck the girl about 1:20 a.m. Sunday when she ran into the 
street as she and family members were getting out of a car, police said. They 
said that when Letts got out of his car to check the girl's condition, the 
girl's father, Kalanda Brooker, 28, a friend of Brooker's and at least one 
neighbor attacked Letts. 
</P>
<P>
When police arrived, Letts was still on the ground with one of his assailants 
kicking him in the head. 
</P>
</TEXT>
