<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRAWL BETWEEN HENDERSON, HALL REPORTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York Yankees' teammates Rickey Henderson and Mel Hall brawled in the 
training room at Comiskey Park on Saturday, according to a published report 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Henderson and Hall were joking before the Yankees' game against the Chicago 
White Sox when the incident escalated into a brawl that had to be broken up by 
Manager Dallas Green and other players, the New York Daily News reported in 
today's editions. 
</P>
<P>
Green rushed in from the manager's office at the other end of the clubhouse to 
help stop the fight. 
</P>
<P>
"You get that a lot in a clubhouse," Green said. "It doesn't bother me as long 
as it's not serious. It's all forgotten today." 
</P>
<P>
The outfielders are reportedly good friends. 
</P>
<P>
Afterward, Henderson hit a game-winning three-run homer as the Yankees beat 
Chicago 5-2. 
</P>
<P>
Neither Hall, on the disabled list with a strained hamstring, nor Henderson 
would discuss the incident. Before Sunday's 6-2 loss to the White Sox, both 
were talking as if nothing had happened. 
</P>
<P>
"Something like that starts out as fun," Green said. "They're fooling around, 
and then it gets more serious as it goes along." 
</P>
</TEXT>
