<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVER KILLED IN FESTIVAL BOAT RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WENATCHEE, Wash. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 40-year-old Renton man died after the limited-class hydroplane he was driving 
in the Apple Blossom Festival race flipped and tossed him into the Columbia 
River. He was run over by another boat. 
</P>
<P>
Vernon Haworth was pronounced dead on arrival at Central Washington Hospital 
Sunday afternoon, said Alma Holcomb, nursing supervisor. The accident occurred 
at about 4:45 p.m., during the next to the last race in the regatta. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the other boat, Brad Mosier, was not injured. 
</P>
